Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteModule(25.10)                                        deleteModule(25.10)

Name
       deleteModule  - Deletes a hierarchical instance and it's module and op-
       tionally, its cell

Syntax
       deleteModule

       <moduleName>

       [-help]

       [-cell | -cells ]

       Deletes a hierarchical instance and it's  module  and  optionally,  its
       cell.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each deleteModule parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteModule.

       -cell  Deletes the module of the hierarchical instance. It  only  works
              when  the specified hierarchical instance is the last one in the
              design that references this module.

       -cells Deletes all submodules that are hierarchically inside the module
              from which the given hierarchical instance <moduleName>  is  in-
              stantiated.  If  a submodule is multi-referenced and all sibling
              hierarchical instances instantiated from the submodule are hier-
              archically inside the <moduleName>  hierarchical  instance,  the
              submodule  will be deleted. Otherwise, the multi-referenced sub-
              module will not be deleted.

       <moduleName>
              Specifies the hierarchical instance to delete.

Examples
              * The following command deletes instance RESULTS_CONV_INST:

                deleteModule DTMF_INST/RESULTS_CONV_INST

              * The following command deletes instance  RESULTS_CONV_INST  and
                deletes its cell:

                deleteModule DTMF_INST/RESULTS_CONV_INST -cell

